# Self-Review Before Completion

Before marking any task or feature as complete, review all changes against this checklist:

- [ ] Error handling: Are all failure modes handled? No bare `catch` blocks?
- [ ] Input validation: Are inputs validated at system boundaries?
- [ ] Edge cases: Have boundary conditions been considered (empty inputs, nulls, large data, concurrent access)?
- [ ] Naming: Are all names clear and consistent with the rest of the codebase?
- [ ] Complexity: Can any part be simplified without losing clarity?
- [ ] No leftover TODOs/FIXMEs that should be resolved before submission
- [ ] Public interfaces have clear contracts (documented parameters, return types, error conditions)
- [ ] No unnecessary dependencies or imports added
- [ ] Tests pass and cover the new/changed behavior
